<subSubSection id="C30D6511FFE9FFD7E38C53458A6F9AA6" pageId="1" pageNumber="200" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA8369AFFE9FFD7E38C53458A6F9AA6" blockId="1.[151,1437,1332,1503]" pageId="1" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis id="B963EA88FFE9FFD7E38C534589529A53" bold="true" box="[151,266,1332,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="200">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Mandible with at least four teeth, fourth tooth between tooth one and two, a fifth tooth present in some species between teeth two and three. Eyes bare or essentially so. Fore wing with vein r arising from or distal half of stigma or next to its middle. Metasoma with at least some degree of lateral compression in female. Body elongate. Parasitoids of 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D19FFE9FFD7E22C53D189999AA7" box="[311,449,1440,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chloropidae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C174D19FFE9FFD7E2CA53D18A749AA6" box="[465,556,1440,1467]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
